---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About DevToolKit" description="Learn about DevToolKit, a privacy-first suite of developer utilities.">
  <main class="container static-page-container">
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
      <h1>About <span class="gradient-text">DevToolKit</span></h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
        A premium, zero-latency developer suite built for speed, privacy, and productivity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="padding: 4rem; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
      <h2>Our Philosophy: 100% Client-Side</h2>
      <p>
        In an era where every small utility site wants to upload your sensitive JSON files, API keys, or proprietary PDF documents to their servers, DevToolKit takes a different approach.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>We believe your data should never leave your machine.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        Every single tool on DevToolKit runs entirely within your browser's local sandbox. Whether you're formatting a massive JSON payload, encoding a secure token, or extracting pages from a confidential PDF, all processing happens locally using modern Web APIs and WebAssembly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="padding: 4rem; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
      <h2>The Tech Stack</h2>
      <p>DevToolKit is built on modern web technologies to ensure lightning-fast performance:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Astro</strong> - For static site generation and zero-JS baseline</li>
        <li><strong>Vanilla JavaScript</strong> - For maximum performance and minimal overhead</li>
        <li><strong>PDF-lib</strong> - For complex local PDF manipulation</li>
        <li><strong>Web Workers</strong> - To ensure the UI never blocks during heavy calculations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="padding: 4rem;">
      <h2>Open Source & Privacy First</h2>
      <p>
        DevToolKit has no tracking cookies, no analytics that follow you around, and absolutely no server-side data collection. The code that manipulates your data is running right in front of you.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 2.4rem;">
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Back to Tools</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
